      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 2006 Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution IX MR in concours condition. This chassis retains its factory-spec 4G63 engine featuring MIVEC technology and a twin-scroll turbocharger, delivering linear power through a precise six-speed close-ratio manual transmission. The drivetrain remains undisturbed, utilizing the Active Center Differential (ACD) and rear mechanical limited-slip differential for optimal torque vectoring. Suspension geometry is bolstered by factory-tuned Bilstein monotube dampers, while braking performance is managed by four-piston front Brembo calipers over ventilated rotors. This example exhibits zero oxidation on the undercarriage and factory-original paint depth. Inside, the Recaro upholstery and Alcantara inserts show no bolster wear, reflecting its meticulous preservation.",
